i></b><hr> I have two things I'd like to ask about regarding Beastlords.  My first question is a fairly simple one to answer.  As a hybrid class, shouldn't Beastlords be able to melee immediately after casting a spell?  I've noticed that they have to wait out the full delay like robed casters and priests do, unlike their hybrid siblings.  It kinda makes using spells like Fleeting Fury pointless--you end up spending half of the spell's duration waiting for your first swing.  Is this something that will be corrected, or are things Working as Intended™?<br>____<br><br>Second, since the Beastlord's damage mitigation ability is so weak, and the boosted pet heal series (some of the best pet heals in the game) leads me to believe that the pets were meant to tank, shouldn't the pets be able to taunt a MOb off of me while I'm in melee range?  I know that some code was put in awhile back to stop this from happening, but it seems Beastlords don't work quite the same as robed pet-casting classes.  We were meant to get our hands dirty  =).  Any chance we can get back the ability to share the bruises with our pets?<br><br>Thanks for your time!<br><br><br>Rrash<br>Beastlord of Lanys<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><img src="http://home.swbell.net/sdspies/images/caederesig.jpg" BORDER="0" WIDTH="216"HEIGHT="212" alt="Image courtesy The Ferret Company http://www.ferretcompany.com/"align="left" hspace="15"></p><div align="center"><center><table width="270" height="212">  <tr>    <td width="270" align="center"><font color="#0000FF"><strong>Caedere Draconis</strong></font></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td width="270" align="center"><font color="#0000FF"><strong>Ranger of the 40th Storm</strong></font></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td width="270" align="center"><font color="#0000FF"><strong>Pathfinder of the 12th Lost    Level</strong></font></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td width="270" align="center"><hr></td>  </tr>  <tr>    <td width="270" align="